\033[31m> Commit messages must follow the "Conventional Commits" guideline:\033[0m
https://www.conventionalcommits.org/

\033[32mfeat\033[0m:     A new feature 
\033[32mfix\033[0m:      A bug fix 
\033[32mdocs\033[0m:     Documentation only changes 
\033[32mstyle\033[0m:    Changes that do not affect the meaning of the code (white-space, formatting, missing semi-colons, etc) 
\033[32mrefactor\033[0m: A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature 
\033[32mperf\033[0m:     A code change that improves performance 
\033[32mtest\033[0m:     Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests
\033[32mbuild\033[0m:    Changes that affect the build system or external dependencies (example scopes: gulp, broccoli, npm)
\033[32mci\033[0m:       Changes to your CI configuration files and scripts (example scopes: Travis, Circle, BrowserStack, SauceLabs)
\033[32mchore\033[0m:    Updates that don't modify src or test files (example scopes: updating build tasks, package manager configs)
\033[32mrevert\033[0m:   A revert of a previous commit
\033[32mwip\033[0m:      A work in progress commit that should not be included in the final project history

\033[32m> Syntax:\033[0m
  <type>[optional scope]: <description>

  [optional body]

  [optional footer]

\033[32m> Example:\033[0m
  feat(users): add user login functionality

  This commit adds the ability for users to log in to the application,
  using their email address and password. It also includes some basic
  validation of user input.

  Closes #123\n
